259 63 "What general formula do the above calculations in  suggest? 2^
n" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 388 "5. \+
 Pascal's Triangle.  Recall the definition of Pascal's Triangle.   Use
 Maple to construct the first 10 rows of Pascal's Triangle. (The trick
 will be to get the coefficients to occur in the correct order.  The M
aple command for generating a sequence might be helpful. It is   seq(e
xpression(i),i=m..n);   where expression(i) is an expression with inde
x i and m..n is a range of numbers." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }
